---

Slice the @Sugar Snap Peas{80} in half lengthways.

Trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{210} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. 
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Noodles ==

While the chicken browns, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{0.25%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} to the water and cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

== Stir-Fry ==

Once the chicken has browned, add the sugar snaps, @Red Thai Style Paste{50} and
garlic to the pan.

Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, carrot ribbons, @Ketjap Manis{50}, @Sugar{½} and
@Water{50} to the pan. Stir together until well combined and piping hot, then
remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

Share the Thai inspired chicken noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5} to finish.

Enjoy!